wiki_section_text: Pope Urban V died on December 20 , 1370 , at Avignon . He was the first Pope who resided in Rome since 1304 , although only for a short time ( 1367 until the beginning of 1370 , when he returned to Avignon ) . At the time of his death , there were 20 living Cardinals . Eighteen of them participated in the conclave : [ 1 ]

intro: The papal conclave of 1370 (December 29-30), held after the death of Pope Urban V, elected as his successor cardinal Pierre Roger de Beaufort, who under the name Gregory XI became seventh and the last Pope of the period of Avignon Papacy.
